          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The neutrons were generated using deuteron beam",
                "to bombard a deuterium gas target in pressure 0.30",
                "MPa, the intensity of the deuteron beam was about 2.5",
                "uA and the length of the target gas cell was 2.0 cm.",
                "The deuterium gas target was separated from the",
                "vacuum tube of the accelerator by a molybdenum",
                "membrane 5.0 um in thickness. The gas target was",
                "cooled by a compressed air jet."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A twin-gridded ionization chamber was used as",
                "the charged particle detector. The distances from",
                "cathode to grid and anode to grid were 6.1 and 1.5",
                "cm, respectively. The working gas Kr+CO2(2.7%)",
                "pressures were 0.052 MPa for 4.0-5.0 MeV region and",
                "0.068 MPa for 5.5-6.0 MeV region, respectively."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A BF3 long counter located at 0 degree with",
                "respect to the deuteron beam axis was used to",
                "monitor the relative neutron fluence. The outer",
                "radius of the BF3 long counter was 27 mm and its",
                "length was 300 mm. The BF3 long counter was",
                "surrounded by a moderator with radius of 350 mm and",
                "length of 400 mm, and a cadmium plate 0.5 mm in",
                "thickness was mounted at the front face of the",
                "counter. The distance between the front face of the",
                "BF3 long counter and the center of the gas target was",
                "about 3.0 m."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "12-MG-25",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.986
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The material of the 25Mg sample",
                "is 25MgO. The sample radius was 22.0 mm. The 25Mg",
                "nucleus number of forward and backward direction were",
                "1.623 x E20 (+-5%) and 1.580 x E20 (+- 5%),",
                "respectively. The tantalum backing layers with 0.1 mm",
                "thick were faced with each other."
              ]
            }
          ],
